  "packageName": "@cubid/stellar",
  "readme": [
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": "# "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`@cubid/stellar`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": "\n\nStellar-oriented Cubid wallet/provider helpers built on top of "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`@cubid/core`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": ".\n\n## When To Choose This Package\n\nUse "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`@cubid/stellar`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": " when you need Stellar-specific public wallet metadata,\nprovider-adapter, and verification helpers. Choose "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`@cubid/web3`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": " only when you\nstill depend on the older shared wallet surface.\n\n## Install\n\n"
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "```sh\nnpm install @cubid/stellar @cubid/core\n```"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": "\n\n## Registry Availability\n\n- npm: supported\n- JSR: not published by policy\n\n## API Reference\n\n- JSON reference: "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`../../docs/reference/api/stellar.json`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": "\n- Package matrix: "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`../../README.md`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": "\n\n## Connection Model\n\n"
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`@cubid/stellar`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": " treats wallet "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`address`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": " as the primary identity for default\nstamp serialization. Optional "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`federationAddress`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": ", "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`networkPassphrase`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": ", and "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`publicKey`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": "\nmetadata may be preserved on the connection when a host wallet exposes them.\n\n## Capability Metadata\n\nStellar connections may expose optional "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`capabilities`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": " metadata for features that\nare not universal across host wallet providers or adapters, such as:\n\n- "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`smartAccount`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": "\n- "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`sessionKeys`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": "\n- "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`paymaster`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": "\n- "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`gasSponsorship`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": "\n\nThese descriptors are intentionally opt-in and capability-driven.\n\nThe package exports "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`getCubidStellarCapabilities(...)`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": " and\n"
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`hasCubidStellarCapability(...)`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": " so host apps can read that metadata without\nassuming any advanced custody feature is universally available.\n\nThis package does not create wallet keys, perform normal transaction signing,\noperate an MPC provider, or broadcast transactions. Host apps or specialist\nwallet providers own those responsibilities."
    }
  ]
}
